A few weeks ago, I was invited to @joannaczechofficial Studio in NYC for a LYMA Laser Facial. And boy was I in for a treat. Read More about the treatment I received and why I am highly recommending you book your session AND SOON! #notanad 

The 60-minute LED Facial is an abbreviated version of their signature treatment. The great thing is that it is customized to each client’s skin on the day of treatment, which means no two facials will be identical.

My treatment began with sculpting and lifting, manual massage, exfoliation, and a combination of targeted serums explicitly chosen for my skin’s needs. Afterward, my esthetician incorporated a few modalities— which included various forms of microcurrent, ultrasound, cryotherapy, oxygen infusion, serums, and masks. I highly recommend this luxurious treatment. I left feeling and looking better than when I walked in. I’m excited about returning next month. 

Check out their website to view the complete list of their offerings. #LymaLaserFacial #joannaczechofficial #selfcare

A Year Older, A Park of Reflection. As I take another lap around the sun, I find myself in the midst of Washington Square park, where A-LOT of life-transforming milestones unfolded for me. Coming from humble beginnings in the Caribbean, where the simple luxury of fragrance seemed out of reach, I now revel in the ability to choose from a multitude of scents. And this fall, my go-to companion is Replica By the Fireplace. 

Described by the brand as an evocative fragrance, By the Fireplace transports me to cozy evenings filled with warmth and comfort. It intertwines the smoky essence of burning wood with the delicate notes of gaiac wood, cashmere, and clove oil. With a harmonious blend of chestnut and red berries, it recreates the scent of roasted chestnuts, adding a touch of nostalgia to this olfactory journey. 

As I close my eyes, inhaling this captivating fragrance, I am reminded of how far I’ve come, from a place where dreams seemed distant to a moment where possibilities are boundless…. #1111

If you are new to this space, it may come as a surprise that throughout my professional trajectory, I have consistently adhered to the conventional 9-5 work schedule for as long as my recollection serves me. Assuming leadership positions, where I have the privilege to steer and motivate individuals, provides me with an immense sense of fulfillment. 

Nevertheless, several years ago, an urge to nurture my artistic side propelled me to take on blogging, primarily as an outlet for my creativity. Unfortunately, at some point along this journey, my passion for it gradually diminished. I am uncertain whether this decline in passion stems from the oversaturation of content creators in the market or simply my own inability to allocate adequate time. 

However, regardless of the cause, I AM committed to sharing MY workwear-friendly looks every Monday (from now on) until the end of this year. I may even sprinkle in a few holiday-inspired ensembles, should the opportunity arise #kenskloset 

Have a great Monday Beautiful People.!

Growing up in the Caribbean, the limited options for fashion meant that standing out from the crowd was a challenge. And, I despise blending in, so I took it upon myself to unleash my creativity and make the most of what I had in my wardrobe - which wasn’t much. I would experiment with unconventional methods such as turning clothes upside down, wearing dresses backwards, tie-dyeing shoelaces, and finding multiple ways to wear a single item. Looking back, I now realize that I was likely the only one daring to do so, although it was not a conscious decision.

In keeping with that same spirit, today’s outfit features a unique twist. I decided to wear my skirt upside down because I loved how it flowed and added an extra touch of flair to my look.

Remember, true magic happens when you dare to break free from the confines of fashion norms and play outside the margins, even if it’s just a little bit.
